    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "The way that I saw this was that we don't need identifiers. At the end of the day, with the Configure render state, you want to know what are _all_ the search parameters that it applied.\r\n\r\nSo I think it's fine to merge all the Configure render state properties in there—with a priority to the last props if duplicated, just like how `searchParameters` are sent to Algolia.\r\n\r\nWdyt?",
